Package de.halirutan.mathematica.parsing.prattParser.parselets

Interface Summary
InfixParselet Interface for all parselets that implement an infix operation.
PrefixParselet Interface for all prefix operator parselets.

DerivativeParselet Parselet for derivative expression like f''[x] or g' I expect the left operand to be a symbol.
FunctionCallParselet Parses functions calls like f[x] and array element access like l[[i]] since both start with an opening bracket.
GroupParselet Parselet for grouping (2+3)*4
ImplicitMultiplicationParselet This parselet is special, because it is not bound to a special operator.
InfixCallParselet This parses infix calls of functions.
InfixOperatorParselet Parselet for all non-special binary infix operators like *, +, ==.
ListParselet Parses constructs like {1,2,3}
MessageNameParselet Parselet for MessageName's like blub::usage or Sin::argx.
NumberParselet Parselet for numbers.
ParserUtil Utility class for parsing.
PatternParselet Parselet for MessageName's like blub::usage or Sin::argx.
PostfixOperatorParselet Parselet for typical postfix operators like a! or i++
PrefixBlankNullSequenceParselet Parses ___expr.
PrefixBlankParselet Parses _expr.
PrefixBlankSequenceParselet Parses __expr.
PrefixOperatorParselet Parselet for a typical prefix operator like ++a or !a which does not need special care.
PrefixSpanParselet Parses Span constructs like list[[;;]] or list[[;;i]] where ;; is a prefix operator.
SpanParselet Parses Span constructs.
StringParselet Parsing a string.
SymbolParselet Parselet for symbols (identifier).
TagSetParselet Parselet for all tag setting operations like a /: b = c or a /: b =.
